### County in [Qinghai](/Qinghai), [China](/China)

#### Zadoi County

The name itself sounds like a sigh. [杂多县](/Simplified_Chinese_characters) · རྫ་སྟོད་རྫོང་།. Or perhaps, [Dzatö, Dzatoe, Zaduo](/Dzatö,_Dzatoe,_Zaduo). Whichever way you slice it, it's a [County](/County_(People's_Republic_of_China)), a designation that implies a certain order, a structure that probably doesn't exist here.

It's located in the southwest of [Qinghai Province](/Qinghai), China. A place that borders the [Tibet Autonomous Region](/Tibet_Autonomous_Region) to the south. Imagine that. A boundary. As if geography matters when everything else is falling apart. It's under the administration of [Yushu Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture](/Yushu_Tibetan_Autonomous_Prefecture). The county seat, if you can call it that, is in the Town of [Qapugtang](/Qapugtang). A name that rolls off the tongue like gravel.

