Zadoi County ([Tibetan](/Tibetan_script): རྫ་སྟོད་རྫོང་།; [Chinese](/Simplified_Chinese_characters): 杂多县) is a county in the southwest of [Qinghai Province](/Qinghai), China, bordering the [Tibet Autonomous Region](/Tibet_Autonomous_Region) to the south. It is under the administration of [Yushu Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture](/Yushu_Tibetan_Autonomous_Prefecture). The county seat is in the Town of [Qapugtang](/Qapugtang).

It's a geographical footnote, a place defined by its borders and its superiors. Under the administration of... like a prisoner under guard. The county seat, a town named [Qapugtang](/Qapugtang), which sounds like a forgotten dialect.

